.TH man 1 "19 April 2017" "0.0" "HSH"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- super simple command interpreter
At this stage does not use the PATH and all commands can be excuted starting
with /bin/command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
\fBFORMAT
\fB[ARGUMENT(S)]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
The shell project is part of Holberton school curriculu\
m and this custom shell suppose to replicate some of the functionalities of sh.
Display a prompt and wait for the user to type a command. A command line always ends with a new line. The prompt is displayed again each time a command has been executed.If an executable cannot be found,  an error message will be printed and the prompt will be displayed  again.
.SH OPTIONS
.B ./hsh
Supports some standard aliases
.I ls -l
.I ls -la
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
Report any found bugs to 128@holbertonschool.com or katya@holbertonschool.com
.SH EXIT STATUS
exits with code 0 on "end of file" condition. `CTRL + D`. Otherwise the shell will return the exit status of the last command executed, or if the exit builtin is used with a numeric argument, it will return the argument.
.SH EXAMPLES
.I /bin/ls - prints content of the current directory
.I /bin/pwd - prints the path of the current working directory
.SH AUTHORS
